1
00:00:00,970 --> 00:00:03,950
Hey, all you viewers out there!

2
00:00:03,950 --> 00:00:07,120
When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make 
sure to keep the room nice and bright,

3
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:09,360
and sit back from the screen, 'kay?

4
00:00:13,550 --> 00:00:15,820
I bet I'll scare the pants 
off Happy with this!

5
00:00:15,820 --> 00:00:18,250
Even Erza might be surprised!

6
00:00:19,930 --> 00:00:21,080
Wait...

7
00:00:21,740 --> 00:00:24,920
I bet Lucy's reaction would 
be the best of the bunch!

8
00:00:26,070 --> 00:00:29,340
This is the end for you. Get it, Boy?

9
00:02:02,130 --> 00:02:06,250
Damn it! My transmissions to Wally 
and Millianna are being intercepted!

10
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:09,140
Now I don't have any idea where they are!

11
00:02:09,140 --> 00:02:10,150
Transmissions?

12
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,900
Telepathic Communication Magic, yes?

13
00:02:17,420 --> 00:02:19,290
Are you okay, Sho?

14
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:20,780
Yeah.

15
00:02:21,770 --> 00:02:24,240
Since you're here for me...

16
00:02:29,230 --> 00:02:31,230
Heaven's Game!

17
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:39,550
Hey, can we really trust him?

18
00:02:39,550 --> 00:02:43,320
I accept that he wasn't 
trying to kill us, but...

19
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,360
I have no intention of making excuses.

20
00:02:45,990 --> 00:02:47,680
You heard me then?

21
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:53,860
Any wizard that'd die from something 
like that would be no match for Jellal.

22
00:02:54,330 --> 00:02:59,030
And I was confident that Natsu wouldn't die.

23
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:01,090
Uh, what about me, then?

24
00:03:01,090 --> 00:03:05,120
You people haven't realized 
Natsu's true power.

25
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:09,050
When Natsu obtains the 
true power of the dragon,

26
00:03:09,050 --> 00:03:10,940
he will destroy all evil before him!

27
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:14,290
I can't wipe around my mouth!

28
00:03:14,290 --> 00:03:15,710
Eww!

29
00:03:15,710 --> 00:03:18,010
Maybe I really should take this off...

30
00:03:18,010 --> 00:03:19,420
Wait, it won't come off!

31
00:03:19,420 --> 00:03:21,550
Goodbye, Boy...

32
00:03:23,310 --> 00:03:23,990
What?

33
00:03:23,990 --> 00:03:26,720
Don't!

34
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,720
Millianna?

35
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:27,640
It's the blockhead!

36
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:29,020
What are you doing?

37
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:34,070
No bullying kitty-cats!

38
00:03:34,070 --> 00:03:37,350
That's not a cat! Just look at him!

39
00:03:42,540 --> 00:03:43,950
Why, you...

40
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:45,070
Out of the way, Millia!

41
00:03:45,070 --> 00:03:47,030
He's an enemy, get it?

42
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:48,290
Take this!

43
00:03:52,830 --> 00:03:54,460
Cat Barrier!

44
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:57,040
The kitty-cat!

45
00:03:57,040 --> 00:04:00,210
I told you, it's not a cat! It's an enemy!

46
00:04:01,670 --> 00:04:04,610
An enemy? Even though it's a kitty-cat?

47
00:04:04,610 --> 00:04:06,510
There's a person inside!

48
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:12,020
Cat Fire!

49
00:04:16,770 --> 00:04:20,710
Not bad. I can see why Jellal 
said to watch out for you, Boy.

50
00:04:20,710 --> 00:04:22,930
Millia, back me up!

51
00:04:23,290 --> 00:04:27,190
Pretending to be a kitty cat when you're 
a person? That's totally un-spiffy!

52
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:28,450
You're one to talk!

53
00:04:28,450 --> 00:04:30,880
Cat-ch you tubes!

54
00:04:31,660 --> 00:04:33,930
Excellent work, Millianna.

55
00:04:33,930 --> 00:04:36,000
Wally, get that impostor cat!

56
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,750
Just watch, Millia!

57
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:40,080
Cat Fire!

58
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:40,550
Huh?

59
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:45,090
What the...

60
00:04:45,090 --> 00:04:47,300
I can't use magic all of a sudden!

61
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:49,390
Is it this thing's fault?

62
00:04:53,390 --> 00:04:55,190
I hate impostor cats!

63
00:05:00,220 --> 00:05:02,730
That's as far as you go, Salamander.

64
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,860
Die!

65
00:05:04,860 --> 00:05:06,110
This ain't good!

66
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:10,330
Oops. I almost forgot to 
say my dandy catch phrase.

67
00:05:10,330 --> 00:05:13,030
From the moment you met me...

68
00:05:13,030 --> 00:05:14,960
...your fate was sealed...

69
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:17,760
Happy!

70
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,090
Natsu, I'm so glad you're safe!

71
00:05:20,090 --> 00:05:22,340
And wait, what's with the helmet?

72
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:24,310
Whatever, just help me get free!

73
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:25,050
Aye!

74
00:05:25,050 --> 00:05:28,380
Why that... How dare you 
interrupt my catch phrase!

75
00:05:29,590 --> 00:05:30,960
Don't!

76
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:32,860
Don't bully kitty-cats!

77
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:34,350
Cats can't fly!

78
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:36,880
I'll let the talking slide, but the flying?

79
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:37,980
Happy, now's our chance!

80
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:39,150
Aye, sir!

81
00:05:39,150 --> 00:05:40,260
Not on your life!

82
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:42,360
I said don't!

83
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,240
Let me go!

84
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:46,340
Hurry up, Happy!

85
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:48,700
This thing's not coming off so easy!

86
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:53,030
Damn it... I'm gonna have to do that!

87
00:05:53,030 --> 00:05:55,860
Secret Move!

88
00:05:55,860 --> 00:05:57,830
Cat in Distress.

89
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,260
Whoa, it worked!

90
00:06:11,260 --> 00:06:13,310
What are you doing, Millianna?

91
00:06:13,310 --> 00:06:15,900
But the kitty-cat was...

92
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:17,090
No buts!

93
00:06:17,090 --> 00:06:18,570
All righty then!

94
00:06:18,570 --> 00:06:20,770
Go forth, Natsu!

95
00:06:21,730 --> 00:06:23,730
Wing Slash of the Fire Dragon!

96
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:31,110
My revenge on the blockhead is complete!

97
00:06:31,670 --> 00:06:34,260
How long do you plan on wearing that?

98
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:36,580
I can't get it off...

99
00:06:53,710 --> 00:06:56,340
Sho and Simon have turned against me.

100
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:02,730
Wally and Millianna have 
fallen to Salamander.

101
00:07:02,980 --> 00:07:09,560
This is how it should be. There is nothing 
more boring than a one-sided game.

102
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:14,200
Lord Jellal, let us hurry and 
capture Erza to begin the ceremony.

103
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:17,330
This is no longer the time 
to be playing around.

104
00:07:17,650 --> 00:07:21,040
Then why don't you go, Vidaldus?

105
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:24,040
Are you sure?

106
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:27,400
It's our turn next, yes?

107
00:07:46,670 --> 00:07:49,650
The Assassin's Guild, Death's Head Caucus.

108
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:52,480
Vidaldus Taka.

109
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,400
Go to hell!

110
00:07:54,400 --> 00:08:00,040
Hell! I'll show you the lowest 
pits of the ultimate hell!

111
00:08:00,380 --> 00:08:01,540
Fukuro.

112
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:08,750
And their commander, Ikaruga.

113
00:08:09,540 --> 00:08:14,660
Love and life are fated 
to be broken asunder, yes?

114
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:21,020
This eve shall be a festival.

115
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:24,450
We are from the Death's Head 
Caucus of the Assassin's Guild.

116
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:29,230
The Special Guerrilla Squad: 
Trinity Raven, have arrived.

117
00:08:29,910 --> 00:08:32,260
It's your turn now.

118
00:08:32,830 --> 00:08:33,900
Go.

119
00:08:43,310 --> 00:08:44,790
H-Happy!

120
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:45,420
What?

121
00:08:45,730 --> 00:08:48,950
P-Pull harder!

122
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:52,320
I'm pulling as hard as I can!

123
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:55,280
You're gonna tear my head off!

124
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,430
It came off!

125
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:03,820
Now it's the blockhead who's trapped!

126
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:07,150
I wonder what's with that mask's head-hole?

127
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:10,380
Our showdown isn't over yet, Salamander!

128
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,530
I've already paid you back.

129
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:18,810
And since Erza and Happy are safe, I 
don't have any reason to keep fighting.

130
00:09:18,810 --> 00:09:20,330
Yeah!

131
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:24,330
We're going to heaven!

132
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:28,740
The true freedom that Jellal talks about...

133
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:32,170
The world where we can rule...

134
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:35,420
Welcome, everyone, to the Tower of Heaven.

135
00:09:35,420 --> 00:09:36,840
Jellal!

136
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,850
I am Jellal.

137
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:42,470
The ruler of this tower.

138
00:09:42,470 --> 00:09:45,000
Both of our pieces are in place.

139
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:45,810
What?

140
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:50,310
It's Jellal. He can be 
heard throughout the tower.

141
00:09:52,330 --> 00:09:54,900
Isn't it about time to get things started?

142
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:58,110
Heaven's Game!

143
00:09:58,110 --> 00:10:00,040
A game?!

144
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,570
Jellal!

145
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:04,230
The rules are simple.

146
00:10:04,230 --> 00:10:09,240
I wish to use Erza as the living sacrifice 
to hold the ceremony to resurrect Zeref.

147
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:13,070
Jellal...

148
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:17,750
In other words, if the door to 
heaven opens, victory is mine.

149
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:20,800
If you can prevent me from doing that,

150
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,750
then you win.

151
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:26,690
However that alone would not be any fun.

152
00:10:26,690 --> 00:10:29,560
So I have assembled three warriors.

153
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:31,610
Three warriors?

154
00:10:31,610 --> 00:10:32,900
Who?

155
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:37,070
If you cannot overcome them, 
then you will not reach me.

156
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:40,950
In other words it is a 3 vs. 8 battle royal.

157
00:10:41,970 --> 00:10:44,200
Oh, and one final thing.

158
00:10:44,530 --> 00:10:50,530
It is possible that the Magic Council will 
attack this place from the Satellite Square.

159
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:57,260
With the ultimate magic that returns 
everything to nothingness, Etherion!

160
00:10:57,260 --> 00:10:58,920
That wasn't in the deal, Jellal!

161
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:03,880
You bastard! We get hit with that, 
and we're all going to hell!

162
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:06,120
Vidaldus, my dear...

163
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,220
Might you be turning tail?

164
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:10,750
No, the total opposite!

165
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,620
Reverse!

166
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:14,600
This is the ultimate high!

167
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:17,570
I've been waiting for a 
dangerous job like this!

168
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,950
No one knows how long we have left.

169
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:24,870
But when Etherion is fired, 
everything will be wiped out.

170
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:28,910
The game will be over, with no players left.

171
00:11:28,910 --> 00:11:30,970
What is he thinking?

172
00:11:30,970 --> 00:11:32,540
Etherion?

173
00:11:33,190 --> 00:11:34,790
The Council is doing what?

174
00:11:35,380 --> 00:11:36,870
I don't believe it.

175
00:11:42,130 --> 00:11:43,180
Erza!

176
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:44,640
Sho, what are you doing?

177
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:46,970
Now...

178
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,850
Let's have fun.

179
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:52,660
I won't let anyone harm Sister!

180
00:11:52,660 --> 00:11:54,470
Hey, Sho!

181
00:11:54,470 --> 00:11:57,610
I will defeat Jellal myself!

182
00:11:57,610 --> 00:11:59,530
Stop this! It's impossible alone!

183
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:02,850
All right! I'm all fired up!

184
00:12:02,850 --> 00:12:07,070
I suppose this Jellal guy 
is at the top, right?

185
00:12:07,070 --> 00:12:09,090
What are you doing, Jellal?

186
00:12:09,090 --> 00:12:13,580
Etherion? If that's fired, 
then everyone will...

187
00:12:14,330 --> 00:12:18,860
All we ever wanted was true freedom...

188
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:22,760
I don't know what kinda 
freedom you're searchin' for,

189
00:12:23,540 --> 00:12:26,420
but the freedom we have in 
Fairy Tail is pretty awesome.

190
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:29,280
Happy!

191
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:31,640
There are ways to cheat at games, right?

192
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:32,310
Aye!

193
00:12:34,490 --> 00:12:36,560
Let's head to the very top right away!

194
00:12:36,910 --> 00:12:38,520
Aye, sir!

195
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,930
Salamander...

196
00:12:43,310 --> 00:12:47,560
That's a nice... scarf... you've got...

197
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,250
Something's coming.

198
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:19,360
What the heck was that?

199
00:13:20,420 --> 00:13:21,890
Salamander!

200
00:13:21,890 --> 00:13:24,320
Huh? Who are you?

201
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:27,760
Natsu, he's one of the blockhead's buddies!

202
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:30,660
Which means you're one of Jellal's lackeys?

203
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:33,610
No! I'm on your side!

204
00:13:33,610 --> 00:13:37,330
I was always just pretending 
to be fooled by Jellal.

205
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:40,580
In order to stop him.

206
00:13:40,580 --> 00:13:42,400
I don't believe you!

207
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,510
Wait.

208
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,590
That's true?

209
00:13:45,590 --> 00:13:46,730
Yes.

210
00:13:47,820 --> 00:13:50,580
Who is this Jellal guy?

211
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:54,040
Why'd he set up this idiotic game?

212
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:57,760
He's the younger twin brother of a 
member of the Magic Council, Siegrain.

213
00:13:58,190 --> 00:14:02,610
He must have realized ahead of time 
that the council would use Etherion.

214
00:14:02,610 --> 00:14:05,480
What, it's some fight between brothers?

215
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,900
I wonder about that...

216
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:12,020
Even I don't have any idea 
what happened between them.

217
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,040
That's...

218
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:20,770
I will not permit you to break the rules!

219
00:14:20,770 --> 00:14:24,300
I will pass judgment upon 
you in the name of justice!

220
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:27,640
The Warrior of Justice, Fukuro, is here!

221
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,690
It's a bird!

222
00:14:29,690 --> 00:14:31,800
That bird's blabbing about justice?

223
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:34,510
Oh, no... Dark Moment!

224
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:39,040
I can't see!

225
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:41,040
I knew it, he's the enemy!

226
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,380
Now's your chance!

227
00:14:42,380 --> 00:14:44,240
Go! Don't even try to take that guy on!

228
00:14:44,990 --> 00:14:46,570
Fine.

229
00:14:46,570 --> 00:14:49,820
The Owl of Justice can see 
through the darkness!

230
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:53,830
Justice Hoo-Hoo-Hoot!

231
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:56,710
How do you like it?

232
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:58,160
Hey, are you okay?

233
00:14:59,420 --> 00:15:03,460
Then... This must be the Assassin's 
Guild, Death's Head Caucus!

234
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:05,710
Assassin's Guild?

235
00:15:05,710 --> 00:15:08,080
One of the dark guilds.

236
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,510
They don't do proper jobs.

237
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:14,850
They're the worst kind of guild that 
specializes in assassination requests!

238
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:18,740
And the three person team 
called, "Trinity Raven,"

239
00:15:18,740 --> 00:15:23,020
assassinated every officer in the 
Western Army in the Cabria War!

240
00:15:23,020 --> 00:15:24,490
They're a legendary unit!

241
00:15:24,490 --> 00:15:28,710
And that guy's one of the members 
of the squad? Er... flock?

242
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,530
I only eliminated evil!

243
00:15:32,260 --> 00:15:34,480
He's a professional assassin!

244
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:35,660
You can't fight him!

245
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:41,540
Salamander! Your evil deeds 
have reached our guild's ears!

246
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:44,460
Today this warrior of justice 
will bury your evil!

247
00:15:46,230 --> 00:15:50,700
Guilds are places where our trust 
and dreams are gathered together.

248
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:53,220
They ain't places for doin' dirty work!

249
00:15:53,220 --> 00:15:55,290
Stand back, Salamander!

250
00:15:55,290 --> 00:15:58,350
You can't fight members of the Assassin's Guild!

251
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:02,230
I don't like those assassination jobs.

252
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:05,540
I don't like the people 
who request 'em, either.

253
00:16:05,540 --> 00:16:08,730
I don't like that you call it a guild.

254
00:16:08,730 --> 00:16:11,320
And because I don't like 
'em, I'm gonna bust 'em up!

255
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:13,950
Bring it on, birdbrain!

256
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:17,580
So naive, Salamander!

257
00:16:17,580 --> 00:16:21,320
There is evil in this world 
that cannot be left alive!

258
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:22,500
Thrusters!

259
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:28,040
You are one of those who 
should best disappear!

260
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:31,130
Jet! Hoo-Hoo-Hoot!

261
00:16:31,130 --> 00:16:32,050
Natsu!

262
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:39,050
I ain't gonna lose to fire, buddy!

263
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:42,060
Thrusters, once again!

264
00:16:50,770 --> 00:16:52,670
Throw!

265
00:16:53,180 --> 00:16:53,940
Natsu!

266
00:16:55,580 --> 00:16:57,030
Oww!

267
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:01,850
You're pretty sturdily built there.

268
00:17:01,850 --> 00:17:04,710
This will be a rare job worth doing!

269
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:09,020
Trinity Raven... They're 
beyond even the rumors...

270
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:11,470
And there are three of them?

271
00:17:13,850 --> 00:17:19,220
How pitiful, Simon. And 
the game has just begun.

272
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:25,570
So next we have Fukuro vs. Natsu Dragneel.

273
00:17:25,570 --> 00:17:29,150
I had hoped Natsu would get to the top,

274
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:32,870
but perhaps he's at a disadvantage.

275
00:17:32,870 --> 00:17:34,480
Natsu!

276
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:36,790
Natsu-san!

277
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:38,840
Natsu!

278
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:44,780
He's got really sharp ears, so he should 
be able to hear us from anywhere.

279
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:46,800
Same as Gajeel-kun, then.

280
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,620
In that case his nose should also be good.

281
00:17:48,620 --> 00:17:49,860
You call him "-kun?"

282
00:17:48,620 --> 00:17:54,380
Note: -kun is an honorific used for young boys and people lower than your status.

283
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:54,380
I wonder why Juvia is searching for 
Natsu-san together with you, Lucy-san?

284
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:56,030
Ignoring me, I see?

285
00:17:56,030 --> 00:17:59,030
Um, what else can we do?

286
00:17:59,030 --> 00:18:03,940
I'm worried about Erza, 
so I'm going after Sho!

287
00:18:03,940 --> 00:18:06,630
I'll leave you two to find Natsu.

288
00:18:06,630 --> 00:18:09,270
I shall do it for Gray-sama's sake,

289
00:18:09,270 --> 00:18:11,730
but to be stuck with one's rival in love...

290
00:18:11,730 --> 00:18:14,140
I can only imagine the 
carnage that will ensue!

291
00:18:14,460 --> 00:18:17,080
Look, I'm trying <i>really</i> hard 
not to be involved in this.

292
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,740
Let's get along, 'kay?

293
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:23,100
What's that horrible noise?

294
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:24,330
A guitar?

295
00:18:24,330 --> 00:18:25,930
Man, that's loud!

296
00:18:25,930 --> 00:18:28,130
Juvia thinks he's pretty good.

297
00:18:28,130 --> 00:18:31,120
Something is wrong with you, seriously.

298
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:56,820
It's a live performance from hell! Destroy!

299
00:18:58,110 --> 00:18:59,250
Get a haircut!

300
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,950
The Assassin's Guild, Death's Head Caucus!

301
00:19:01,950 --> 00:19:05,730
It means skull, get it? 
Pretty awesome name, huh?

302
00:19:05,730 --> 00:19:08,410
The three warriors that Jellal 
was talking about, then?

303
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:11,080
I'm one of Trinity Raven.

304
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:13,920
Vidaldus Taka, that's me!

305
00:19:15,180 --> 00:19:17,500
Rock you!

306
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:28,990
Hey, you got an interesting body there.

307
00:19:30,710 --> 00:19:33,840
Juvia's body is made of water.

308
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:35,020
Drip, drip, drop.

309
00:19:35,020 --> 00:19:36,860
Go get 'im, Juvia!

310
00:19:36,860 --> 00:19:38,500
I'll just get out of your way, and...

311
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:41,320
There is no attack that 
will work against Juvia.

312
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:43,780
Water Lock!

313
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:46,810
Rock?

314
00:19:46,810 --> 00:19:48,410
You're a rocker too?

315
00:19:52,820 --> 00:19:54,450
Nothing but talk.

316
00:19:54,450 --> 00:19:56,350
You weren't one of the Element 4 for nothing!

317
00:19:56,350 --> 00:19:57,920
You'd be pretty scary as an enemy...

318
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:26,210
Juvia's Water Lock has disappeared!

319
00:20:26,210 --> 00:20:27,850
And... Eww!

320
00:20:27,850 --> 00:20:31,010
It's best to wash out your hair 
with water in the morning.

321
00:20:31,010 --> 00:20:33,580
Shampooing every day will damage your hair.

322
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:36,880
You bastard... How did 
you break the Water Lock?

323
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:39,930
My hair can absorb liquid.

324
00:20:39,930 --> 00:20:44,420
But no oil or alcohol, please... 
That would damage it.

325
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:46,900
Water is ineffective?

326
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:48,090
Oh, no!

327
00:20:48,090 --> 00:20:52,120
But you girls ain't so bad looking!

328
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:54,420
There it is! As usual!

329
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:55,690
What are you talking about?

330
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:58,830
"Being cute is the source 
of all my troubles."

331
00:20:58,830 --> 00:21:03,260
Eeny-meeny-miny-moe...

332
00:21:03,260 --> 00:21:09,200
Which-one-will-be-come-my-hell's-min-ion?

333
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,390
All set!

334
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:12,910
You'll be my succubus today!

335
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:17,450
Succubus?

336
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:20,360
Rock of Succubus!

337
00:21:26,210 --> 00:21:27,930
What is this sound?

338
00:21:30,470 --> 00:21:32,710
No, stop it!

339
00:21:32,710 --> 00:21:34,680
Juvia, what's wrong?

340
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:37,770
Don't! Don't come inside Juvia!

341
00:21:43,090 --> 00:21:45,900
So that's as far as the water woman goes, eh?

342
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:47,820
And, at the same time...

343
00:21:50,290 --> 00:21:51,240
Juvia!

344
00:21:55,370 --> 00:21:57,210
Become my slave!

345
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:06,890
Hell, hell, hell!

346
00:22:06,890 --> 00:22:10,710
I'll show you the lowest 
pits of the ultimate hell!

347
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:16,600
What's happened?

348
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:22,620
...the Spirit user is also out of the game.

349
00:23:56,170 --> 00:24:01,030
I heard that Erza was lonely and 
couldn't get close to anyone as a kid.

350
00:24:01,030 --> 00:24:03,220
I can't even imagine it now.

351
00:24:03,220 --> 00:24:08,210
I bet that she puts on a tough shell to 
protect her heart from the pain of her past.

352
00:24:08,210 --> 00:24:10,460
Well she <i>is</i> always wearing armor...

353
00:24:10,460 --> 00:24:13,470
That's not what I meant. I 
mean she closes off her heart.

354
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:16,470
Next time: Heart's Armor.

355
00:24:16,470 --> 00:24:20,000
Uh, you're talkin' too complicated. 
I don't get you, Happy.

356
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,050
That's 'cause you're full-open, Natsu.

357
00:24:22,050 --> 00:24:24,360
Oven? We baking somethin'?

358
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:26,610


